<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, viewport-fit=cover" />
  <title>Cookie Policy | View</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Cookie Policy for View by Ceetify. Learn how cookies, local storage, and similar technologies are used on the View platform." />
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#0f172a" />
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />

  <style>
    :root{
      --bg:#07111f;
      --bg2:#0b1628;
      --card:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
      --card2:rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
      --text:#eaf2ff;
      --muted:#a9bbd6;
      --line:rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
      --blue:#3b82f6;
      --cyan:#22d3ee;
      --red:#ef4444;
      --green:#22c55e;
      --amber:#f59e0b;
      --shadow:0 20px 50px rgba(0,0,0,0.35);
      --radius:24px;
      --max:1120px;
    }

    *{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
    html{scroll-behavior:smooth}

    body{
      font-family:Inter,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;
      color:var(--text);
      line-height:1.65;
      min-height:100vh;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(34,211,238,.10), transparent 28%),
        radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(59,130,246,.12), transparent 25%),
        linear-gradient(180deg,#07111f 0%,#081322 38%,#0b1628 100%);
      overflow-x:hidden;
    }

    a{color:#9ed0ff;text-decoration:none}
    a:hover{text-decoration:underline}

    .noise{
      position:fixed;
      inset:0;
      pointer-events:none;
      opacity:.06;
      background-image:radial-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,.35) .7px, transparent .7px);
      background-size:18px 18px;
      z-index:0;
    }

    .page{position:relative;z-index:1}

    .topbar{
      position:sticky;
      top:0;
      z-index:50;
      backdrop-filter:blur(14px);
      background:rgba(7,17,31,.78);
      border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .topbar-inner{
      width:min(100% - 24px, var(--max));
      margin:auto;
      display:flex;
      align-items:center;
      justify-content:space-between;
      gap:16px;
      padding:14px 0;
    }

    .brand{
      display:flex;
      align-items:center;
      gap:12px;
      min-width:0;
    }

    .brand-badge{
      width:46px;
      height:46px;
      border-radius:14px;
      display:grid;
      place-items:center;
      font-weight:900;
      color:#fff;
      background:linear-gradient(135deg,#ef4444,#3b82f6);
      box-shadow:var(--shadow);
      flex-shrink:0;
    }

    .brand-text h1{
      font-size:1rem;
      line-height:1.1;
      font-weight:800;
    }

    .brand-text p{
      color:var(--muted);
      font-size:.84rem;
      white-space:nowrap;
      overflow:hidden;
      text-overflow:ellipsis;
    }

    .nav{
      display:flex;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      gap:10px;
      justify-content:flex-end;
    }

    .nav a{
      display:inline-flex;
      align-items:center;
      justify-content:center;
      padding:10px 14px;
      border-radius:999px;
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      background:rgba(255,255,255,.04);
      color:var(--text);
      font-size:.92rem;
      transition:.25s ease;
    }

    .nav a:hover{
      text-decoration:none;
      transform:translateY(-1px);
      background:rgba(255,255,255,.08);
      border-color:rgba(255,255,255,.2);
    }

    .hero{
      width:min(100% - 24px, var(--max));
      margin:34px auto 22px;
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns:1.18fr .82fr;
      gap:22px;
    }

    .hero-card,.summary-card,.section,.toc,.contact-card{
      background:linear-gradient(180deg,var(--card),var(--card2));
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius:var(--radius);
      box-shadow:var(--shadow);
      backdrop-filter:blur(12px);
    }

    .hero-card{
      padding:28px;
      position:relative;
      overflow:hidden;
    }

    .hero-card::before{
      content:"";
      position:absolute;
      width:260px;
      height:260px;
      right:-90px;
      top:-90px;
      border-radius:50%;
      background:radial-gradient(circle, rgba(59,130,246,.18), transparent 70%);
      pointer-events:none;
    }

    .eyebrow{
      display:inline-flex;
      align-items:center;
      gap:8px;
      padding:8px 12px;
      border-radius:999px;
      border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.22);
      background:rgba(59,130,246,.08);
      color:#dceeff;
      font-size:.86rem;
      margin-bottom:14px;
    }

    .hero h2{
      font-size:clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.1rem);
      line-height:1.02;
      margin-bottom:14px;
      letter-spacing:-.03em;
    }

    .hero p.lead{
      color:var(--muted);
      font-size:1.05rem;
      max-width:760px;
    }

    .meta{
      display:flex;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      gap:12px;
      margin-top:20px;
    }

    .meta span{
      padding:10px 14px;
      border-radius:999px;
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      background:rgba(255,255,255,.05);
      font-size:.92rem;
      color:#dce8ff;
    }

    .summary-card{
      padding:22px;
      display:flex;
      flex-direction:column;
      gap:12px;
      justify-content:center;
    }

    .summary-card h3{
      font-size:1.15rem;
      font-weight:800;
    }

    .summary-item{
      padding:14px;
      border-radius:18px;
      background:rgba(255,255,255,.04);
      border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);
    }

    .summary-item strong{
      display:block;
      margin-bottom:4px;
      font-size:.96rem;
    }

    .summary-item span{
      color:var(--muted);
      font-size:.92rem;
    }

    .layout{
      width:min(100% - 24px, var(--max));
      margin:0 auto 48px;
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns:320px 1fr;
      gap:22px;
      align-items:start;
    }

    .toc{
      position:sticky;
      top:92px;
      padding:18px;
    }

    .toc h3{
      font-size:1rem;
      margin-bottom:12px;
      font-weight:800;
    }

    .toc a{
      display:block;
      padding:11px 12px;
      border-radius:14px;
      color:#dbeafe;
      font-size:.94rem;
      border:1px solid transparent;
      transition:.2s ease;
    }

    .toc a:hover{
      text-decoration:none;
      background:rgba(255,255,255,.06);
      border-color:rgba(255,255,255,.08);
    }

    .content{
      display:grid;
      gap:18px;
    }

    .section{
      padding:26px;
    }

    .section h3{
      font-size:1.35rem;
      font-weight:800;
      margin-bottom:12px;
      letter-spacing:-.01em;
    }

    .section h4{
      font-size:1rem;
      margin:18px 0 10px;
      color:#dfeeff;
      font-weight:800;
    }

    .section p{
      color:var(--muted);
      margin-bottom:12px;
    }

    .section ul{
      padding-left:20px;
      color:var(--muted);
      margin:10px 0 14px;
    }

    .section li{
      margin-bottom:8px;
    }

    .pill-row{
      display:flex;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      gap:10px;
      margin-top:10px;
    }

    .pill{
      padding:9px 12px;
      border-radius:999px;
      background:rgba(59,130,246,.10);
      border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.22);
      color:#dceeff;
      font-size:.9rem;
    }

    .highlight{
      padding:16px 18px;
      border-radius:18px;
      background:rgba(34,197,94,.08);
      border:1px solid rgba(34,197,94,.18);
      color:#dafce7;
      margin-top:14px;
    }

    .note{
      padding:16px 18px;
      border-radius:18px;
      background:rgba(245,158,11,.08);
      border:1px solid rgba(245,158,11,.18);
      color:#ffe6b8;
      margin-top:14px;
    }

    .contact-card{
      width:min(100% - 24px, var(--max));
      margin:0 auto 36px;
      padding:24px;
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
      gap:18px;
      align-items:center;
    }

    .contact-card h3{
      font-size:1.35rem;
      margin-bottom:8px;
    }

    .contact-card p{
      color:var(--muted);
    }

    .contact-actions{
      display:flex;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      gap:12px;
      justify-content:flex-end;
    }

    .btn{
      display:inline-flex;
      align-items:center;
      justify-content:center;
      padding:13px 18px;
      border-radius:14px;
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      text-decoration:none;
      color:#fff;
      transition:.25s ease;
      font-weight:700;
    }

    .btn.primary{
      background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--blue),var(--cyan));
      border:none;
    }

    .btn.secondary{
      background:rgba(255,255,255,.05);
    }

    .btn:hover{
      text-decoration:none;
      transform:translateY(-1px);
      opacity:.97;
    }

    footer{
      width:min(100% - 24px, var(--max));
      margin:0 auto 40px;
      color:var(--muted);
      text-align:center;
      padding:10px 0 40px;
      font-size:.92rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 980px){
      .hero,.layout,.contact-card{
        grid-template-columns:1fr;
      }
      .toc{
        position:relative;
        top:0;
      }
      .contact-actions{
        justify-content:flex-start;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 700px){
      .topbar-inner{
        align-items:flex-start;
        flex-direction:column;
      }

      .nav{
        width:100%;
        justify-content:flex-start;
      }

      .hero-card,.summary-card,.section,.toc,.contact-card{
        border-radius:20px;
      }

      .hero-card,.summary-card,.section{
        padding:20px;
      }

      .meta span{
        width:100%;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="noise"></div>

  <div class="page">
    <header class="topbar">
      <div class="topbar-inner">
        <div class="brand">
          <div class="brand-badge">V</div>
          <div class="brand-text">
            <h1>View Cookie Policy</h1>
            <p>View by Ceetify — Cookies, storage, and similar technologies</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <nav class="nav">
          <a href="/index.html">Home</a>
          <a href="/privacy.html">Privacy</a>
          <a href="/terms.html">Terms</a>
          <a href="/contact.html">Contact</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-card">
        <div class="eyebrow">Cookies • Local Storage • Sessions</div>
        <h2>How View uses cookies and similar technologies.</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          This Cookie Policy explains how View may use cookies, local storage,
          session storage, browser storage, pixels, and similar tools to keep the
          platform working, improve user experience, maintain security, and support
          analytics and notifications.
        </p>

        <div class="meta">
          <span><strong>Effective date:</strong> March 30, 2026</span>
          <span><strong>Platform:</strong> View by Ceetify</span>
          <span><strong>Contact:</strong> info.ceeticegroup@gmail.com</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="summary-card">
        <h3>Quick summary</h3>

        <div class="summary-item">
          <strong>Why we use them</strong>
          <span>To sign you in, keep sessions active, remember settings, improve performance, and support security.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="summary-item">
          <strong>What may be used</strong>
          <span>Cookies, local storage, session storage, cache, device identifiers, and related tools.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="summary-item">
          <strong>Your control</strong>
          <span>You may control some storage through browser or device settings, but some features may stop working properly.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="summary-item">
          <strong>Related policy</strong>
          <span>This page should be read together with the View Privacy Policy.</span>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="layout">
      <aside class="toc">
        <h3>Contents</h3>
        <a href="#what-are-cookies">1. What Cookies Are</a>
        <a href="#what-we-use">2. What We Use</a>
        <a href="#why-we-use">3. Why We Use Them</a>
        <a href="#essential">4. Essential Technologies</a>
        <a href="#performance">5. Performance & Analytics</a>
        <a href="#preferences">6. Preferences & Convenience</a>
        <a href="#security">7. Security & Fraud Prevention</a>
        <a href="#push">8. Notifications, Tokens & Device Storage</a>
        <a href="#third-party">9. Third-Party Services</a>
        <a href="#manage">10. How to Manage Them</a>
        <a href="#changes">11. Changes to This Policy</a>
        <a href="#contact-us">12. Contact Us</a>
      </aside>

      <main class="content">
        <section class="section" id="what-are-cookies">
          <h3>1. What Cookies Are</h3>
          <p>
            Cookies are small data files that websites can store on your browser
            or device. Similar technologies include local storage, session storage,
            cached files, browser memory, scripts, device identifiers, and other
            tools that help websites and apps remember actions or settings.
          </p>
          <p>
            Some technologies are needed for the platform to work properly, while
            others help improve speed, security, settings, or measurement.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="what-we-use">
          <h3>2. What We Use</h3>
          <p>Depending on how View is built and used, the platform may use:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Browser cookies</li>
            <li>Local storage</li>
            <li>Session storage</li>
            <li>Cached files and offline storage</li>
            <li>Device or browser tokens for push notifications</li>
            <li>Authentication session data</li>
            <li>Security-related storage tools</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="pill-row">
            <span class="pill">Cookies</span>
            <span class="pill">Local storage</span>
            <span class="pill">Session storage</span>
            <span class="pill">Push tokens</span>
            <span class="pill">Offline cache</span>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="why-we-use">
          <h3>3. Why We Use Them</h3>
          <p>View may use these technologies for purposes such as:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Keeping users signed in securely</li>
            <li>Remembering app or site preferences</li>
            <li>Maintaining sessions between pages or reloads</li>
            <li>Supporting performance and loading speed</li>
            <li>Helping detect suspicious activity or abuse</li>
            <li>Enabling notification or device-specific features</li>
            <li>Understanding feature usage and product performance</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="essential">
          <h3>4. Essential Technologies</h3>
          <p>
            Some storage and cookie-like technologies are necessary for View to function.
            Without them, important parts of the platform may not work correctly.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Sign-in and account authentication</li>
            <li>Secure session handling</li>
            <li>Page navigation consistency</li>
            <li>Account state and access control</li>
            <li>Basic fraud and abuse protection</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="highlight">
            Essential technologies are usually required for core platform features
            such as login, access control, and security.
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="performance">
          <h3>5. Performance & Analytics</h3>
          <p>
            View may use measurement or analytics-related storage to understand how
            the platform performs and how users interact with features.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Page and feature usage measurement</li>
            <li>Error tracking and debugging support</li>
            <li>Performance improvement</li>
            <li>Feature testing and product optimization</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            This helps us improve speed, reliability, and user experience across
            the platform.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="preferences">
          <h3>6. Preferences & Convenience</h3>
          <p>
            Some technologies help remember choices you make so you do not need to
            re-enter them each time.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Theme or appearance settings</li>
            <li>Language or region preferences</li>
            <li>Navigation state</li>
            <li>Dismissed notices or prompts</li>
            <li>Saved interface preferences</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="security">
          <h3>7. Security & Fraud Prevention</h3>
          <p>
            View may use cookies or similar storage for security, abuse detection,
            and fraud prevention.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Protecting against suspicious login behavior</li>
            <li>Identifying repeated abuse or automated misuse</li>
            <li>Protecting sessions from unauthorized access</li>
            <li>Supporting moderation and risk controls</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="note">
            Some security-related storage may remain necessary even when other
            optional technologies are limited.
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="push">
          <h3>8. Notifications, Tokens & Device Storage</h3>
          <p>
            If View supports browser or device notifications, your device or browser
            may create identifiers or tokens needed to send those notifications.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Push subscription tokens</li>
            <li>Notification permission states</li>
            <li>Service worker cache or offline assets</li>
            <li>Installable app-related storage for PWA features</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Disabling certain browser storage may affect notifications, offline use,
            or installable app features.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="third-party">
          <h3>9. Third-Party Services</h3>
          <p>
            Some third-party tools integrated into View may also use cookies or similar
            technologies, depending on how the platform is configured.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Authentication providers</li>
            <li>Analytics providers</li>
            <li>Embedded media or social integrations</li>
            <li>Security, hosting, or infrastructure services</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Those third parties may have their own policies and data practices.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="manage">
          <h3>10. How to Manage Them</h3>
          <p>
            You may be able to manage cookies and similar storage through your browser,
            device, or app settings.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Clear cookies and site data in your browser settings</li>
            <li>Block some cookies through browser privacy controls</li>
            <li>Clear local storage and cached site data</li>
            <li>Disable or manage notification permissions from device or browser settings</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Please note that limiting or removing certain technologies may affect
            login, saved preferences, notifications, and other View features.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="changes">
          <h3>11. Changes to This Policy</h3>
          <p>
            We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes
            in View, our technical setup, legal requirements, or platform features.
          </p>
          <p>
            When updates are made, the effective date at the top of this page may
            also be updated.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="contact-us">
          <h3>12. Contact Us</h3>
          <p>
            If you have questions about this Cookie Policy or how storage-related
            technologies are used on View, contact us:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>App:</strong> View</li>
            <li><strong>Company:</strong> Ceetify / Ceetify Multi-Ventures Ltd</li>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info.ceeticegroup@gmail.com">info.ceeticegroup@gmail.com</a></li>
            <li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://view.ceetice.com">view.ceetice.com</a></li>
          </ul>

          <div class="highlight">
            For broader information about data collection and use, please also read
            the View Privacy Policy.
          </div>
        </section>
      </main>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-card">
      <div>
        <h3>Want to understand how your data is handled?</h3>
        <p>
          Read the full privacy details or contact support for questions about
          cookies, storage, sessions, or notifications on View.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="contact-actions">
        <a class="btn primary" href="/privacy.html">View Privacy Policy</a>
        <a class="btn secondary" href="/contact.html">Contact Support</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer>
      © 2026 View by Ceetify. All rights reserved.
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
